Honourable Moshood Salvador, chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC) will soon formally announce his defection to the Labour Party (LP). Moshood, a former Chairman of Lagos State People’s  Democratic Party (PDP) defected to the ruling party with a large fellowship, and while in the APC he constituted a political group, the Conscience Forum, which membership is reported to be numbering hundreds of thousands. However, Daily Independent gathered from a reliable source that the chieftain who is planning his defection will be running as the gubernatorial candidate of the Labour party in Lagos State. The ground is set as members of the party popularly called the Third Force are ready to break the news on a date yet to be scheduled. Also, the candidates of the House of Representatives, House of Assembly, Senatorial candidates and a host of others are ready for the event to kick off. Details shortly.